      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so is the money just sitting there in a regular bank account with my name on it? or is like a third party actually holding onto it for us while the deal is happening? i just want to make sure the money is safe until the title actually transfers.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow account is typically held by a third-party escrow agent or a solicitor's trust account, which is a secure, interest-bearing account specifically designed for escrow purposes. The funds are usually deposited into this account by your lender, and then held until the title transfer occurs. This ensures that the funds are safe and protected until the sale is finalized, and the money can't be accessed or spent by either you or the seller until the deal is completed.",
